2.01	William_W._Mercer	William W. Mercer	William W. Mercer is a United States Attorney for the District of Montana, as well as Principal Associate Deputy Attorney General for the United States Department of Justice. In September 2006, Mercer was nominated by George W. Bush as Associate Attorney General, served as Acting Associate Attorney General until June 22, 2007; he resigned from that position days before his confirmation hearing was to take place, and returned to his United States attorney position in Montana.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/William_W._Mercer.jpg/220px-William_W._Mercer.jpg
